data.enText: affecting all or most people, places or things

data.chText: 普遍认为这次会议是成功的。
data.enText: The general opinion is that the conference was a success.

data.chText: 坏天气影响到的范围相当大。
data.enText: The bad weather has been fairly general (= has affected most areas) .

data.chText: 这个一般性原则有一例外。
data.enText: There is one exception to this general principle.

data.chText: 一般情况下他都尽力给予帮助。
data.enText: As a general rule (= usually) he did what he could to be helpful.
This opinion is common among the general population (= ordinary people) .

data.chText: 概括性的；大体的；笼统的
data.enText: including the most important aspects of sth; not exact or detailed

data.chText: 我核查预订情况以便对计划安排些什么活动有个大体的想法。

data.chText: 我大致知道其中的运作原理。
data.enText: I know how it works in general terms .

data.chText: 他们对这个男人作了大致的描述。
data.enText: They gave a general description of the man.

data.chText: 大致的，大概的（方向或地区）
data.enText: approximately, but not exactly, the direction/area mentioned

data.chText: 他们向敌军所在的大致的方向开了枪。
data.enText: They fired in the general direction of the enemy.

data.chText: 非专门的；一般性的；普通的
data.enText: not limited to a particular subject, use or activity

data.chText: 我们在此阶段应保持相当广泛的讨论。

tr: a fact about the whole (as opposed to particular)
example: he discussed the general but neglected the particular

tr: a general officer of the highest rank
the head of a religious order or congregation

example: We are generaled by an incompetent!

tr: prevailing among and common to the general public

example: the shrewdest political and ecumenical comment of our time"- Christopher Morle

tr: not specialized or limited to one class of things
applying to all or most members of a category or group

example: bearing a general resemblance to the original
a general description of the merchandise

value.def: A general is a high-ranking officer in the armed forces, usually in the army.

example.ex: The General's visit to Sarajevo is part of preparations for the deployment of extra troops.
example.tran: 将军造访萨拉热窝是在为增加兵力部署做准备。

value.def: If you talk about the general situation somewhere or talk about something in general terms, you are describing the situation as a whole rather than considering its details or exceptions.

example.ex: The figures represent a general decline in employment.
example.tran: 这些数字显示就业人数总体在下降。

defx.def: If you describe something in general terms, you describe it without giving details.

example.ex: She recounted in very general terms some of the events of recent months.
example.tran: 她约略讲述了近几个月发生的一些事情。

value.def: You use general to describe several items or activities when there are too many of them or when they are not important enough to mention separately.

example.ex: £2,500 for software is soon swallowed up in general costs...
example.tran: 用于软件方面的2,500英镑很快就被一般性费用耗光了。

example.ex: His firm took over the planting and general maintenance of the park last March.
example.tran: 他的公司去年3月接管了公园的绿化和日常维护工作。

value.def: You use general to describe something that involves or affects most people, or most people in a particular group.

example.ex: The project should raise general awareness about bullying.
example.tran: 这个项目将会提高民众对恃强凌弱行径的认识。

value.def: If you describe something as general, you mean that it is not restricted to any one thing or area.

example.ex: ...a general ache radiating from the back of the neck.
example.tran: 从后颈部扩散到全身的疼痛

example.ex: ...raising the level of general physical fitness.
example.tran: 提高全民的身体健康水平

value.def: A general business offers a variety of services or goods rather than just one particular kind.

example.ex: They ran the general store and the farm dairy.
example.tran: 他们经营着杂货店和农场的乳品店。

value.def: General is used to describe a person's job, usually as part of their title, to indicate that they have complete responsibility for the administration of an organization or business.

example.ex: He joined Sanders Roe, moving on later to become General Manager.
example.tran: 他加入了桑德斯·罗公司，后来一路晋升至总经理。

value.tran: （常用于头衔中）首席的，总管的，级别最高的

value.def: General workers do a variety of jobs which require no special skill or training.

example.ex: The farm employed a tractor driver and two general labourers.
example.tran: 农场雇用了一名拖拉机手和两名杂工。

value.tran: （员工）普通的，非专业的，一般的

value.def: General is used to describe a person who has an average amount of knowledge or interest in a particular subject.

example.ex: This book is intended for the general reader rather than the student.
example.tran: 这本书面向一般读者而非学生。

value.tran: （对某方面的知识或兴趣）一般的，泛泛的

value.def: You use in general to indicate that you are talking about something as a whole, rather than about part of it.

example.ex: I think we need to improve our educational system in general...
example.tran: 我认为有必要从整体上改进我们的教育体系。

example.ex: She had a confused idea of life in general.
example.tran: 总的来说，她对生活非常困惑。

value.tran: 总的来说；总体上来看；大体上

value.def: You say in general to indicate that you are referring to most people or things in a particular group.

example.ex: People in general will support us...
example.tran: 总体而言，人们会支持我们的。

example.ex: She enjoys a sterling reputation in law enforcement circles and among the community in general.
example.tran: 总的说来，她在执法界和老百姓当中口碑甚佳。

value.tran: （指某一群体的大多数）总的来说，总体上

value.def: You say in general to indicate that a statement is true in most cases.

example.ex: In general, it was the better-educated voters who voted Yes in the referendum.
example.tran: 通常是那些受教育程度较高的人在全民公决中投赞成票。
